revision.text:
The '''Advance Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (ACSEE)''' is an academic [[A Level ]] [[Test (assessment)|examination]] that is done by Form Six students ([[12th grade]]) across [[Tanzania]] to prepare them for their [[University]] studies. The exams are usually done between late September to early or mid November and they are managed by the [[National Examinations Council of Tanzania]] (NECTA). Students are required to obtain three credits in order to pass the exams.<ref>http://www.necta.go.tz/acsee_results</ref>

