[[File:Romance Languages-World-Map.png|thumb|300x300px|Romance languages-speaking countries]] The '''Romance-speaking world''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://departamento.pucp.edu.pe/educacion/areas-academicas/curriculo-y-didactica/curriculo-y-didactica-publicaciones/language-acquisition-romance-speaking-world-peru/ |title=Language Acquisition in the Romance Speaking World: Peru - Departamento de Educación |publisher=Departamento.pucp.edu.pe |date= |accessdate=2016-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=zM_mBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA11&lpg=PA11&dq=%22romance+speaking+world%22&source=bl&ots=3NON3tnRBn&sig=Jjw_emV91YugiW2lOf_44Nb7chI&hl=es&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjXgKm33dnMAhVCVhQKHbyvAzwQ6AEIOzAD#v=onepage&q=%22romance%20speaking%20world%22&f=false |title=Manual of Language Acquisition - Google Libros |publisher=Books.google.es |date=2014-08-25 |accessdate=2016-05-14}}</ref> '''romanophone''',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=eOUfbeTC-tsC&pg=PA34&lpg=PA34&dq=romanophone+world&source=bl&ots=6FTE_9tEe8&sig=RNGUpG13AMQGhO9u6zxGuMt_X68&hl=es&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjV8rKO39nMAhXEchQKHWpKDz8Q6AEIKzAB#v=onepage&q=romanophone%20world&f=false |title=Multilingualism, Education and Change - Jean Jacques Weber - Google Libros |publisher=Books.google.es |date= |accessdate=2016-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=_ZmZ21jOH9EC&pg=RA1-PT73&lpg=RA1-PT73&dq=romanophone+world&source=bl&ots=_cr4zsurbj&sig=uvULSkNQRekUZGj5KE_iJ7IEwx8&hl=es&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjV8rKO39nMAhXEchQKHWpKDz8Q6AEIMDAC#v=onepage&q=romanophone%20world&f=false |title=Language in the Media: Representations, Identities, Ideologies - Google Libros |publisher=Books.google.es |date=2007-09-19 |accessdate=2016-05-14}}</ref> '''neolatin world''',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=hprLhm1Xra0C&pg=PA221&lpg=PA221&dq=%22neolatin+world%22&source=bl&ots=Vg3NgueagA&sig=51bkC6eCsXxC2l4K-y_9jgNfhGg&hl=es&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwio5uul39nMAhWCyRQKHSRzC1EQ6AEISDAH#v=onepage&q=%22neolatin%20world%22&f=false |title=I nomi dei fiumi, dei monti, dei siti: strutture linguistiche preistoriche - Claudio Beretta - Google Libros |publisher=Books.google.es |date= |accessdate=2016-05-14}}</ref> or '''Latin-speaking world''',<ref>{{cite journal|author= |title=Radiation oncology in Latin speaking countries: A link between Europe and Latin America. |date=2015-09-28 |pmid=25061515 |doi=10.1016/j.rpor.2013.06.004 |pmc=4104016 |volume=19 |journal=Rep Pract Oncol Radiother |pages=227-9 | last1 = Lopez Guerra | first1 = JL | last2 = Rivin | first2 = E | last3 = Guedea | first3 = F | last4 = Ortiz | first4 = MJ}}</ref> is the part of the world where [[Romance languages]] (those derived from Latin) are either official, co-official, or significantly used, comprising [[Latin America]], [[Romance-speaking Europe|Latin Europe]], Romance-speaking Africa and Romance-speaking Asia.
It includes the [[Spanish language|Spanish]]-, [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]-, [[French language|French]]-, [[Italian language|Italian]]-, [[Romanian language|Romanian]]- and [[Catalan language|Catalan]]-speaking communities.
In European countries like this, the 6-continent combined-America model is usually taught.
