{{infobox recurring event | name = Tokers Bowl | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = Defunct | genre = <!-- e.g. natural phenomena, fairs, festivals, conferences, exhibitions ... --> | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "dates=" also works, but do not use both --> | begins = | ends = | frequency = Annually | venue = BC Marijuana Party Bookstore | location = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> | country = [[Canada]] | years_active = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence --> | first = 2002 | founder_name = <!-- or | founders = --> | last = 2005 | prev = | next = | participants = | attendance = | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = ''[[Cannabis Culture (magazine)|Cannabis Culture]]''{{cn|date=April 2017}} | website = {{URL|tokersbowl.com}} | footnotes = }} '''Tokers Bowl''' was an annual [[cannabis]] event held between 2002 and 2005 at [[British Columbia Marijuana Party]] Bookstore, in [[Vancouver]].<ref name=Meliorist/> It was canceled in 2006 following a raid by the [[Vancouver Police]].<ref>{{citation|title=TB5: Tokers Bowl is officially cancelled|publisher=Tokers Bowl|author=Jodie Giesz-Ramsay<!-- maybe -->|work=official website|url=http://www.tokersbowl.com/tb5.html}}</ref>{{secondary source needed|date=April 2017}} It was held in May<ref name=Rosenthal/> or July<ref name=Macleans/> and was described as "like a [[Cannabis Cup]] North".<ref name=Macleans/>
